ENTRY       EC 1.1.1.370                Enzyme
NAME        scyllo-inositol 2-dehydrogenase (NAD+);
            iolX (gene name)
CLASS       Oxidoreductases;
            Acting on the CH-OH group of donors;
            With NAD+ or NADP+ as acceptor
SYSNAME     scyllo-inositol:NAD+ 2-oxidoreductase
REACTION    scyllo-inositol + NAD+ = 2,4,6/3,5-pentahydroxycyclohexanone + NADH + H+ [RN:R09953]
ALL_REAC    R09953
SUBSTRATE   scyllo-inositol [CPD:C06153];
            NAD+ [CPD:C00003]
PRODUCT     2,4,6/3,5-pentahydroxycyclohexanone [CPD:C00691];
            NADH [CPD:C00004];
            H+ [CPD:C00080]
COMMENT     The enzyme, found in the bacterium Bacillus subtilis, has no activity with NADP+ [cf. EC 1.1.1.371, scyllo-inositol 2-dehydrogenase (NADP+)]. It is part of a scyllo-inositol degradation pathway leading to acetyl-CoA.
